transactions = read_csv('data/transactions.csv')
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   id = col_double(),
##   account_id = col_double(),
##   date = col_date(format = ""),
##   type = col_character(),
##   amount = col_double(),
##   balance = col_double(),
##   bank = col_character(),
##   account = col_double(),
##   method = col_character(),
##   category = col_character()
## )
n =as.data.frame(table(transactions$account_id))
n = n[which(n$Freq == max(n$Freq)),]
transactions_1 = transactions[transactions$account_id == n$Var1,]
  1. highest number of transactions - overall
p1=
  ggplot(transactions_1,aes(x=date,y=amount))+
  geom_line()+
  labs(title = "Highest number of transactions through time") +
  xlab("Date") +
  ylab("Amount")
p1

  1. Highest number of transactions - Credit VS Debit
p2 = ggplot(transactions_1,aes(x=date,y=amount))+
  geom_line()+
  labs(title = "Highest number of transactions - Credit VS Debit") +
  facet_wrap(~type)+
  xlab("Date") +
  ylab("Amount")

p2

3.Highest number of transactions - by different methods

p3=
  ggplot(transactions_1,aes(x=date,y=amount))+
  geom_line()+
  labs(title = "Highest number of transactions - by different methods") +
  facet_wrap(~category)+
  xlab("Date") +
  ylab("Amount")
p3

  1. Highest number of transactions - by different categories
p4 = ggplot(transactions_1,aes(x=date,y=amount))+
  geom_line()+
  labs(title = "Highest number of transactions - by different categories") +
  facet_wrap(~method)+
  xlab("Date") +
  ylab("Amount")
p4
